The Minister of Works and Housing, Babatunde Fashola has refuted a widespread statistics claiming that Nigeria has a 17million housing deficit, noting that no such deficit exists anywhere in the world.  The minister who made the clarification during a ministerial briefing at the Presidential Villa stressed that the housing deficit experienced in urban centres are caused by massive rural-urban migration, adding that the government is working towards addressing.  According to Fashola, an official census must be conducted to give a definitive response to Nigeria’s housing deficit situation. Our Correspondent, Raliat Adenekan reports that the Minister while fielding questions on delapidated roads said the Federal Government lacks resources and funds to rehabilitate the Abuja-Lokoja-Uromi Highway.